The paper deals with problems related to the drawing of level graphs, which are a type of graph theory. The paper discusses the complexity of two specific problems, Clustered-Level Planarity and T-Level Planarity, and shows that they are NP-complete in the general case but become polynomial-time solvable when restricted to proper instances. The paper also mentions a linear-time algorithm for testing level planarity. Based on this information, the most likely sub-category is cs.CG (Computational Geometry), followed by cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory), and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
